Citation
Morinaga, G. & Bergmann, P. J. Evolution of fossorial locomotion in the transition from tetrapod to snake-like in lizards. Proc. R. Soc. B. 287, 20200192 (2020).

Summary
This paper compares fossorial locomotion in two types of lizards. The types of lizards are tetrapod-like lizards and snake-like lizards. The data studied proves that snake-like lizards move through sand substrates faster than tetrapod-like lizards.

